add function to read the WaitToKillServiceTimeout&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12409659" author="robert_longson@standardandpoors.com" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2005 23:02:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=15499)&lt;br/&gt;
add function to read the WaitToKillServiceTimeout&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12409660" author="robert_longson@standardandpoors.com" created="Tue, 21 Jun 2005 23:08:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=15500)&lt;br/&gt;
read WaitToKillServiceTimeout and only wait that long&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12409661" author="robert_longson@standardandpoors.com" created="Wed, 22 Jun 2005 18:48:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=15510)&lt;br/&gt;
ensure we finish just before the OS kills us&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12409662" author="robert_longson@standardandpoors.com" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2005 19:39:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=15717)&lt;br/&gt;
creates a thread to stop the service so we don&apos;t get killed by the OS&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Without this fix timeouts of &amp;gt; 1 minute don&apos;t work (at least on Windows XP).&lt;br/&gt;
The OS thinks that the service is stuck and kills it. Timeout errors appear in&lt;br/&gt;
the NT event log. &lt;br/&gt;
The service_control_handler needs to return so the calling OS thread can&lt;br/&gt;
monitor the service stopping. Shutdown needs to happen in another thread.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12409663" author="robert_longson@standardandpoors.com" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2005 20:25:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=15718)&lt;br/&gt;
correction to shutdown time&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
